<html xmlns:o='urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office' xmlns:w='urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40'>
<head><meta charset='UTF-8'>
<style>
  body { font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; margin: 40px; color: #1a1a1a; }
  h1 { font-size: 20pt; color: #1a3a6b; border-bottom: 2px solid #1a3a6b; padding-bottom: 8px; margin-bottom: 6px; }
  h2 { font-size: 13pt; color: #1a3a6b; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .subtitle { font-size: 10pt; color: #555; margin-bottom: 30px; }
  .ticket { border: 1px solid #d0d7e3; border-radius: 6px; padding: 18px 22px; margin-bottom: 22px; page-break-inside: avoid; }
  .ticket-header { background: #1a3a6b; color: #fff; padding: 8px 14px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 11pt; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 14px; display: inline-block; }
  .field-label { font-weight: bold; color: #1a3a6b; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 3px; font-size: 10.5pt; }
  .field-value { font-size: 10.5pt; color: #2a2a2a; margin-left: 0; line-height: 1.6; }
  .screenshot-note { background: #f0f4ff; border-left: 3px solid #4f7ef7; padding: 8px 12px; font-size: 9.5pt; color: #444; margin-top: 8px; font-style: italic; }
  code { background: #f3f3f3; padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 3px; font-family: Consolas, monospace; font-size: 9.5pt; color: #c0392b; }
  .severity-high { color: #c0392b; font-weight: bold; }
  .severity-med { color: #e67e22; font-weight: bold; }
  .severity-low { color: #27ae60; font-weight: bold; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>ShopEase — Bug Fix Tickets</h1>
<div class="subtitle">Project: ShopEase v5 &nbsp;|&nbsp; Platform: Vanilla JS / Azure Static Web Apps &nbsp;|&nbsp; Total Tickets: 10</div>

<!-- BUG-001 -->
<div class="ticket">
  <div class="ticket-header">BUG-001 &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span class="severity-high">HIGH</span></div>
  <div class="field-label">File:</div>
  <div class="field-value"><code>shopease/js/nav.js</code> — Line 10</div>
  <div class="field-label">Description of Issue:</div>
  <div class="field-value">A <code>SyntaxError: Unexpected identifier 'essential'</code> was thrown in <code>nav.js</code> at line 10. Unescaped single quotes inside single-quoted JavaScript strings in the cookies modal <code>onclick</code> handlers caused the entire script to fail at parse time. The attributes <code>onclick="Nav.setCookies('essential')"</code> and <code>onclick="Nav.setCookies('all')"</code> were malformed.</div>
  <div class="screenshot-note">📸 Screenshot provided: Browser DevTools Console showing the error "Uncaught SyntaxError: Unexpected identifier 'essential'" on nav.js:10, alongside a second error on stock.html:50. Console had previously been filtered (showing 'discount' filter) which initially masked the errors.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Escaped the inner single quotes in both <code>onclick</code> handlers so they read <code>Nav.setCookies(\'essential\')</code> and <code>Nav.setCookies(\'all\')</code> respectively.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Test of Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Open the cookies consent modal and click both "Essential Only" and "Accept All" buttons. Verify each button triggers the correct <code>Nav.setCookies()</code> call without throwing a console error and that cookie preferences are saved as expected.</div>
</div>

<!-- BUG-002 -->
<div class="ticket">
  <div class="ticket-header">BUG-002 &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span class="severity-high">HIGH</span></div>
  <div class="field-label">File:</div>
  <div class="field-value"><code>shopease/admin/stock.html</code> — Line 50</div>
  <div class="field-label">Description of Issue:</div>
  <div class="field-value">A <code>SyntaxError: missing ) after argument list</code> was thrown in <code>admin/stock.html</code> at line 50. Broken string concatenation in the emoji picker <code>onclick</code> handler — the expression <code>'" onclick="pe(\'+e+\')" &gt;'</code> was treating <code>+e+</code> as literal string content instead of interpolating the variable, preventing the admin stock page from loading.</div>
  <div class="screenshot-note">📸 Screenshot provided: Browser DevTools Console showing both the nav.js:10 error and the stock.html:50 "missing ) after argument list" SyntaxError. The admin inventory page was rendering blank as a result.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Corrected concatenation to <code>'" onclick="pe(\''+e+'\')" &gt;'</code> so the variable <code>e</code> is properly interpolated outside the quoted string boundaries.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Test of Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Open the admin stock management page and interact with the emoji picker when adding or editing a product. Verify the correct emoji value is passed to <code>pe()</code> with no console errors.</div>
</div>

<!-- BUG-003 -->
<div class="ticket">
  <div class="ticket-header">BUG-003 &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span class="severity-high">HIGH</span></div>
  <div class="field-label">File:</div>
  <div class="field-value"><code>shopease/shop.html</code> — Line 55</div>
  <div class="field-label">Description of Issue:</div>
  <div class="field-value">A <code>SyntaxError: missing ) after argument list</code> was thrown in <code>shop.html</code> at line 55. Broken string concatenation <code>\'+p.name+</code> in the wishlist button <code>onclick</code> handler was treating <code>p.name</code> as literal string content rather than as a variable interpolation, causing the shop catalogue page to fail to render.</div>
  <div class="screenshot-note">📸 Screenshot provided: Browser DevTools Console showing "Uncaught SyntaxError: missing ) after argument list" on shop.html:55, after the nav.js and stock.html errors had been fixed. The shop page was rendering blank.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Corrected the concatenation to <code>\''+p.name+</code> so <code>p.name</code> is concatenated as a variable outside the string. Applied using a Python byte-level replacement due to backslash escaping limitations in the editor.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Test of Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Navigate to the shop page and click the wishlist (heart) button on any product. Verify the correct product name is passed and the item is added to the wishlist with no console errors.</div>
</div>

<!-- BUG-004 -->
<div class="ticket">
  <div class="ticket-header">BUG-004 &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span class="severity-high">HIGH</span></div>
  <div class="field-label">File:</div>
  <div class="field-value"><code>shopease/recommendations.html</code> — Line 29</div>
  <div class="field-label">Description of Issue:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Same broken string concatenation pattern as BUG-003 present in <code>recommendations.html</code> at line 29 in the wishlist <code>onclick</code> handler. <code>\'+p.name+</code> was incorrectly treated as literal string content, causing the recommendations page to throw a SyntaxError and fail to render.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Applied the same fix as BUG-003 — corrected <code>\'+p.name+</code> to <code>\''+p.name+</code> using a Python byte-level replacement.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Test of Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Navigate to the recommendations page and click the wishlist button on any recommended product. Verify the correct product name is passed to the handler and that no console errors are thrown.</div>
</div>

<!-- BUG-005 -->
<div class="ticket">
  <div class="ticket-header">BUG-005 &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span class="severity-high">HIGH</span></div>
  <div class="field-label">File:</div>
  <div class="field-value"><code>shopease/wishlist.html</code> — Line 28</div>
  <div class="field-label">Description of Issue:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Same broken string concatenation pattern <code>\'+p.name+</code> was present in <code>wishlist.html</code> inside the <code>rm()</code> <code>onclick</code> handler. This caused a SyntaxError that prevented the wishlist page from rendering and items from being removed.</div>
  <div class="screenshot-note">📸 Screenshot provided: User reported "same for wishlist and cart" with a browser console screenshot showing the identical SyntaxError pattern appearing on wishlist.html after the shop.html fix was applied.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Corrected <code>\'+p.name+</code> to <code>\''+p.name+</code> using Python byte-level replacement, consistent with the fixes applied in BUG-003 and BUG-004.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Test of Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Navigate to the wishlist page, ensure items are present, then click the remove (heart) button on an item. Verify the item is correctly removed and <code>p.name</code> is passed accurately to <code>rm()</code> with no console errors.</div>
</div>

<!-- BUG-006 -->
<div class="ticket">
  <div class="ticket-header">BUG-006 &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span class="severity-high">HIGH</span></div>
  <div class="field-label">File:</div>
  <div class="field-value"><code>shopease/cart.html</code> — Line 33</div>
  <div class="field-label">Description of Issue:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Same broken string concatenation pattern in <code>cart.html</code> inside the <code>setDel()</code> <code>onclick</code> handler, where <code>\'+k+</code> was being treated as literal string content rather than interpolating the variable <code>k</code>. This caused a SyntaxError preventing the cart page from rendering.</div>
  <div class="screenshot-note">📸 Screenshot provided: Same console screenshot as BUG-005 showing the identical error pattern now appearing in cart.html after wishlist.html was identified.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Corrected <code>\'+k+</code> to <code>\''+k+</code> using Python byte-level replacement, ensuring <code>k</code> is properly passed as a variable to <code>setDel()</code>.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Test of Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Navigate to the cart page with items present and select a delivery option (Standard, Express, Free). Verify <code>setDel()</code> is called with the correct key value and the order summary updates accordingly with no console errors.</div>
</div>

<!-- BUG-007 -->
<div class="ticket">
  <div class="ticket-header">BUG-007 &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span class="severity-med">MEDIUM</span></div>
  <div class="field-label">File:</div>
  <div class="field-value"><code>shopease/shop.html</code> — <code>add()</code> function</div>
  <div class="field-label">Description of Issue:</div>
  <div class="field-value">In <code>shop.html</code>, the <code>add()</code> function was not calling <code>filt()</code> after adding an item to the cart. As a result, the product grid was not re-rendering following an add action, leaving the UI in a stale state — stock levels and button states were not updating to reflect the cart change.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Added a call to <code>filt()</code> immediately after the <code>Nav.toast()</code> call within the <code>add()</code> function, ensuring the product grid re-renders correctly after every add-to-cart action.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Test of Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Navigate to the shop page and add any product to the cart. Verify the product grid re-renders immediately after the toast notification appears and that stock-related UI state (e.g. low stock warnings, disabled buttons) updates correctly.</div>
</div>

<!-- BUG-008 -->
<div class="ticket">
  <div class="ticket-header">BUG-008 &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span class="severity-med">MEDIUM</span></div>
  <div class="field-label">File:</div>
  <div class="field-value"><code>shopease/recommendations.html</code> — <code>add()</code> function</div>
  <div class="field-label">Description of Issue:</div>
  <div class="field-value">In <code>recommendations.html</code>, the <code>add()</code> function was not calling <code>render()</code> after adding an item to the cart. This meant the recommendations list was not refreshing after an item was added, leaving the page displaying stale data and inaccurate stock states.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Added a call to <code>render()</code> immediately after the <code>Nav.toast()</code> call within the <code>add()</code> function so the recommendations list updates correctly after every add-to-cart action.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Test of Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Navigate to the recommendations page and add a recommended product to the cart. Verify the recommendations list re-renders after the toast notification and that stock levels and button states reflect the updated state accurately.</div>
</div>

<!-- BUG-009 -->
<div class="ticket">
  <div class="ticket-header">BUG-009 &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span class="severity-high">HIGH</span></div>
  <div class="field-label">Files Affected:</div>
  <div class="field-value"><code>shop.html</code>, <code>wishlist.html</code>, <code>cart.html</code>, <code>recommendations.html</code></div>
  <div class="field-label">Description of Issue:</div>
  <div class="field-value">All pages were rendering completely blank — no navigation, no products, no content. The root cause was the <code>SyntaxError</code> in <code>nav.js</code> at line 10 (BUG-001). Because <code>nav.js</code> failed at parse time, the entire script was never executed, meaning the <code>Nav</code> object was never defined. Every page that calls <code>Nav.init()</code> therefore failed silently and rendered nothing.</div>
  <div class="screenshot-note">📸 Screenshots provided: (1) Blank shop page with no navigation or products visible — only the page background rendered. (2) Blank admin inventory page with DevTools Elements/Issues tabs open showing no rendered content. (3) Console with 'discount' filter active showing no errors — the filter was masking the real SyntaxErrors. (4) Console with filter removed showing the actual nav.js:10 and stock.html:50 SyntaxErrors clearly.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Resolved entirely by the fix applied in BUG-001. Correcting the syntax error in <code>nav.js</code> allowed the script to parse and execute successfully, making the <code>Nav</code> object available to all dependent pages.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Test of Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Load each affected page (shop, wishlist, cart, recommendations) in the browser after clearing localStorage. Verify all pages render their navigation, content and products correctly with no blank page or <code>Nav is not defined</code> errors in the console.</div>
</div>

<!-- BUG-010 -->
<div class="ticket">
  <div class="ticket-header">BUG-010 &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span class="severity-med">MEDIUM</span> — Security / UX</div>
  <div class="field-label">File:</div>
  <div class="field-value"><code>shopease/index.html</code></div>
  <div class="field-label">Description of Issue:</div>
  <div class="field-value">The login page was publicly exposing demo credentials to all visitors. Two <code>demo-box</code> div elements were visible — one on the Customer tab displaying <code>user@shopease.com / password123</code> and one on the Admin tab displaying <code>admin@shopease.com / admin2025</code>. Additionally, both sets of credentials were pre-filled into the email and password input fields, meaning credentials were visible in plain text to anyone visiting the page.</div>
  <div class="screenshot-note">📸 Screenshots provided: (1) Customer login panel showing the blue demo-box with "Demo: user@shopease.com / password123" clearly visible above the form fields. (2) Admin login panel showing the blue demo-box with "Demo: admin@shopease.com / admin2025" visible above the admin form fields.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Removed both <code>demo-box</code> div elements from the page markup entirely. Cleared all pre-filled <code>value</code> attributes from the email and password input fields so they render blank by default. Added placeholder text instead.</div>
  <div class="field-label">Test of Fix:</div>
  <div class="field-value">Navigate to the login page on both the Customer and Admin tabs. Verify no credentials are visible anywhere on the page, that all input fields are empty on load, and that no <code>demo-box</code> elements are present in the page source.</div>
</div>

</body>
</html>
